Quietust, I hoped you'd reply, as I saw some old posts of yours at the SCUMMVM forums, so I figured you would know allot about SCUMM.  The main thing that facinates me is that Maniac Mansion for the NES actually used SCUMM as opposed to just rewriting the entire game in 6502 assembler.<br /><br />The fact that the game uses a well documented game engine / virtual machine should make this game a prime candidate for ROM hackers, but currently the only Maniac Mansion specific ROM tool that exists is one that extracts the game's script.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=94">Jagasian</a> — Tue May 30, 2006 12:23 pm</p><hr />
